2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 5. Bd2 Bb7 6. e3 {As we know from the lines with
4.Qc2, the main alternative to g2-g3.} Bxc3 $1 {Under the given circumstances,
Black needs to act immediately if he intends to keep the game within Queen's
