12. Qc2 Rc8 13. Rd1 Ba7 $15 {With a very active isolani position. Scheide,H 
(2022)-Gruenwald,A (2014) Bad Blankenburg 2006 (0-1, 43)}) 8... O-O 9. Qc2 d4
10. exd4 Nxd4 11. Nxd4 Qxd4 12. Na4 Qe5+ 13. Qe2 Bd4 14. Qxe5 Bxe5 15. Nc5 b6
16. Nd3 Bd4 $15 {Spiridonov,N (2470)-Hulak,K (2450) Sombor 1980 (0-1, 39)}) (6.
Bg5 h6 7. Bxf6 (7. Bh4 Nd4 8. Qd1 Nf5 9. Bxf6 Qxf6 10. Rc1 Bxc5 $15 {With very
active play.}) 7... Qxf6 8. Nf3 Bxc3+ 9. Qxc3 Qxc3+ 10. bxc3 b6 $1 {The pawn
on c5 is not so important, but the squares and development are.} 11. cxb6 axb6
12. e3 Ke7 (12... Ra4 13. Bd3 Ba6 14. Kd2 Ke7 15. Rhb1 {1/2-1/2 (15) Akopian,V
(2605)-Yudasin,L (2580) Dos Hermanas 1992} Rb8 16. Nd4 Bxc4 17. Nxc6+ dxc6 18.
Bxc4 Rxc4 19. Rb4 $11) 13. Be2 Ra4 14. O-O Ba6 15. Nd2 Ne5 16. Rfb1 Nxc4 17.
