Qe2 c6 13. dxc6 Rc8 $19) (11. c5 dxc5 12. c4 Ne8 13. Bb2 f6 {, followed by ...
Nd6, does not seem to offer White complete compensation for the pawn.}) 11...
Ba6 12. Qa4 Qe8 13. Qb4 e4 14. e3 Qe5 15. Bf1 Bc8 $17 {Potapov,A (2404)
-Debashis,D (2529) Pardubice 2018 (0-1, 32)}) (8. O-O {is examined in Line 34.}
) 8... e5 9. Nd2 Re8 10. O-O Qe7 11. e4 {White is best advised to prevent ...
e5-e4.} (11. Re1 {[%csl Ge2] defends e2 but allows} e4 12. Qc2 Na5 $17 {
, followed by ...Bf5, with a passive position for White.}) (11. e3 {is no
