14. Ba3 Bh3 15. e4 Bxg2 16. Qxg2 {1-0 (31) Senthil,M (2312)-Aaditya,A (1548)
Rajapalayam 2019} Ne7 $15) 11... b6 12. f3 exf3 13. Qxf3 Bb7 14. Ba3 Na5 15. e4
c5 (15... Rxe4 $5 16. Nxe4 Bxe4 17. Qe2 Bxg2 18. Kxg2 Qe8 19. Qxe8+ Rxe8 20. c5
Nc4 21. Bc1 Nd5 $17 {Black has two fantastic knights and the bishop is very
passive.}) 16. Qf4 {McNab,C (2427) -Rowson,J (2558) Hamilton 2004 (0-1, 64)}
Qd7 {[%cal Gd7a4] Threatening ...Qa4.} 17. Qh4 {Hoping for Rxf6.} Qg4 $15) (9.
Qc2 Re8 {Reinforcing the threat ... e5-e4.} 10. Rd1 (10. d5 Na5) 10... e4 11.
Ng5 Bf5 12. Qa4 (12. f3 exf3 $1 13. Qxf5 fxg2 14. Re1 h6 15. Nf3 Ne4 $19) 12...
Qc8 13. d5 Ne5 14. c5 Ned7 15. c6 bxc6 16. dxc6 Nb6 17. Qb3 d5 $19 {Botsari,A 
(2325)-Kiriakov,P (2515) Chalkida 1996 (0-1, 22)}) 9... h6 10. Bxf6 (10. Bh4
$146 {deserves mention.} Bg4 {Threatening ...Bxg4.} (10... g5 $2 11. Nxg5 hxg5
12. Bxg5 Kg7 13. f4 $16) 11. Rb1 Rb8 12. Re1 (12. c5 e4 13. Bxf6 Qxf6 14. Nd2
d5 $11) 12... Re8 13. h3 {It is not easy to suggest anything more constructive.
} Bxf3 14. Bxf6 Qxf6 15. exf3 (15. Bxf3 e4 16. Bg2 Na5 17. Qa4 b6 18. e3 h5 $15
) 15... exd4 16. Rxe8+ Rxe8 17. cxd4 Nxd4 (17... b6 18. Qa4 b5 19. cxb5 Qxd4
$11) 18. Rxb7 Re2 19. Rb8+ Kh7 20. Qd3+ g6 21. f4 Kg7 $11 {With complicated
play and balanced chances.}) 10... Qxf6 11. Rb1 (11. e3 $6 Bg4 {Forcing White
to weaken his kingside.} 12. h3 Bh5 13. g4 Bg6 14. Nd2 Rae8 (14... Bd3 $6 15.
Ne4 $1 Bxe4 16. Bxe4 Qh4 17. Qf3 {With certain white pressure. Simek,P (2231)
-Tichy,V (2260) Czechia 2008 (1-0, 54)}) 15. f4 exf4 16. Rxf4 (16. exf4 Bd3 17.
Rf2 Re3 $19) 16... Qg5 $17 {Black has excellent play against White's
weaknesses.}) 11... Rb8 12. Nd2 Bd7 (12... Bf5 {unnecessarily wastes a tempo,
but is playable nevertheless.} 13. e4 Bd7 14. Nb3 b6 15. f4 Qe7 16. Qd3 {
Shirov,A (2673) -Fernandez Gil,M (2215) Tallinn 2016 (1-0, 43)} Nd8 17. Nd2 Ne6
18. f5 Ng5) (12... Na5 {is another good possibility.} 13. Qa4 b6 14. Nb3 Nxb3
15. axb3 a5 16. e3 h5 $11 17. c5 $6 dxc5 18. dxc5 Bf5 $15) 13. Nb3 Qe7 14. e4
f5 15. exf5 Bxf5 16. Rb2 Rbe8 {Black is well regrouped and has adequate
counterplay.} 17. c5 e4 18. cxd6 cxd6 19. Re1 d5 20. f3 Qf7 21. Nd2 exf3 22.
Bxf3 Rxe1+ 23. Qxe1 Re8 24. Qf2 Bd3 25. h4 b6 $11 {Zaremba,A (2337)-Chudnovsky,
