39,51,37,37,42,37,42,34,27,21,39,40]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. f3 c5 5.
d5 b5 6. e4 d6 7. Bd2 {A solid move, indirectly reducing Black's pressure in
the centre.} a6 {Since White did not start to develop his kingside yet, it
makes sense to maintain the tension.} ({Two recent top games went} 7... Bxc3 8.
Bxc3 b4 9. Bd2 O-O 10. Ne2 (10. Be3 exd5 11. cxd5 Nfd7 12. Ne2 f5 13. exf5 Rxf5
14. Ng3 Re5 15. Kf2 Qh4 16. Qd2 Nf6 17. Rc1 Ba6 {, with good play for Black.
